  "translations": {
    "en": {
      "description": {
        "text": "The outermost climbing crag of the Tyresö Peninsula, located about 600 m further out than Dyviksuddsberget. Essentially, it’s a collection of cliffs within a limited area. Currently, there are around thirty routes, but there’s potential for many more.",
        "method": "llm",
        "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
        "sourceIds": [
          "legacy:uddeuddberget"
        ]
      },
      "sections": {
        "allmant": {
          "title": {
            "text": "General",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:uddeuddberget"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "The outermost climbing crag of the Tyresö Peninsula, located about 600 m further out than Dyviksuddsberget. Essentially, it's a whole collection of cliffs within a limited area. Currently, there are around thirty routes, but there are opportunities for many more.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:uddeuddberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "miljo": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Environment",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:uddeuddberget"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "Most of the routes are on the very steep south face, which is over 25 m at the bottom but narrows as you go up. The west side is quite compact with a range of solid overhangs, giving the wall a portal-like appearance.\n\nSouth and west. The south face gets sunlight earlier than Dyviksudd, making it a good morning crag in the spring and autumn. In summer, the trees in front of the wall provide pleasant shade.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:uddeuddberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "vagbeskrivning": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Directions",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:uddeuddberget"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "Like for the Dyviksudd cliffs. Use the same parking pocket. Under no circumstances park in meeting places or private spots. Continue the road past Dyviksuddsberget until a road branches off to the west and follow this. When the road ends, follow the path down to the water and turn back up to the west into a dip. Uddeuddberget is the third cliff on the right, easily recognizable by its size. The other cliffs are considerably smaller.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:uddeuddberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "kommunikationer": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Transport",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:uddeuddberget"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "As for Dödskalleberget. About a 45-minute walk from the terminus.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:uddeuddberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "access": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Access",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:uddeuddberget"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:uddeuddberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "leder": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Routes",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:uddeuddberget"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:uddeuddberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "kratervaggen": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Crater Wall",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:uddeuddberget"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "The steep wall below Mäusliväggen.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:uddeuddberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "mauslivaggen": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Mäusliväggen",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:uddeuddberget"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "To the north of the west wall, the rock becomes lower and more broken. Many routes can be made here. 100 m north of the main wall is a small reddish wall in a ravine.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:uddeuddberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "vastvaggen": {
          "title": {
            "text": "West Wall",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:uddeuddberget"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "The mountain’s west wall currently has only one route, but there are possibilities for more.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:uddeuddberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "sydvaggen": {
          "title": {
            "text": "South Wall",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:uddeuddberget"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:uddeuddberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "ravinen": {
          "title": {
            "text": "The Ravine",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:uddeuddberget"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "On the overhanging wall along the path before the main wall.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:uddeuddberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "flaskvaggen": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Bottle Wall",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:uddeuddberget"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "At the southern end of the ravine, there is a small wall a bit up the slope on the right side.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:uddeuddberget"
            ]
          }
        },
        "vinylvaggen": {
          "title": {
            "text": "Vinyl Wall",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:uddeuddberget"
            ]
          },
          "body": {
            "text": "This wall is by the water at the second bay, part of Grisselberget. Turn right instead of going up left and pass a few boulder problems on the left side down towards the water.",
            "method": "llm",
            "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
            "sourceIds": [
              "legacy:uddeuddberget"
            ]
          }
        }
      },
      "routes": {}
    }
  }
}
